commit.message: Correct format of docs for normalization functions

Private use codepoints should not be counted as 'control characters'

This is a non-backwards compatible change. It only affects utf8.match,
specifically when '%c' is used. Previously, %c (which is for matching
'control characters') would match private use codepoints, such as those
above U+F0000.

This is very non-intuitive and I doubt that any user of the library
would expect this. (Though, Hyrum's Law...)

Adjust the data tables so that utf8.match does not behave this way.

Add 'normalize_nfc' and 'isnfc' functions

All 19,075 test cases in the official normalization test suite from the
Unicode Consortium pass. Also, a fuzzer was used to test the newly
added functions on more than 250,000,000 other randomly generated
test cases, and its output matched the output of ICU on all of them.
Add files for fuzzing isvalid, clean, invalidoffset functions

commit.message:
Fix utf8.charpattern (#26)

* Fix utf8.charpattern

* Add a test for charpattern.

Revise eliminate goto from parseucd.lua (#24)

* Revise: eliminate goto from parseucd.lua (to update to UCD 12.1)

It is not available in Lua 5.1

As a result I can now run parseucd.lua using Unicode 12.1 data - to
update unidata.h.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Lyons <slysven@virginmedia.com>

* Reformat: adjust layout after making coding changes

Doing this afterwards makes it easier to review the coding changes of the
prior commit - when merging the pair it will be fine to "Squash and merge"
them together.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Lyons <slysven@virginmedia.com>
